    "body": "This bug relates to something that's been on my low-priority TODO list for a very long time: implementing a proper world error state and ingame UI that combines our current messy and inconstant handling of connection/lua/sync errors.\n\nWe should set a flag on `World` to stop the world simulation when we hit one of these errors, and then open the ingame menu.  In this state the normal score screen should be replaced with a custom error panel that elaborates on whatever has gone wrong.\n"
